1
00:00:13,540 --> 00:00:15,780
♪Trap my frame♪

2
00:00:15,980 --> 00:00:20,060
♪Plagues demand I bow in shame♪

3
00:00:20,780 --> 00:00:22,940
♪Snare my soul♪

4
00:00:23,020 --> 00:00:27,100
♪Rules command I swallow my pride♪

5
00:00:27,260 --> 00:00:30,620
♪Mock my way♪

6
00:00:30,900 --> 00:00:34,060
♪Chained me where I must stay♪

7
00:00:34,420 --> 00:00:36,780
♪Taught me to kneel, not to speak♪

8
00:00:37,020 --> 00:00:41,220
♪And to let my life pass by in silence♪

9
00:00:42,100 --> 00:00:44,100
♪But I heard the wind♪

10
00:00:44,220 --> 00:00:45,900
♪From the sea and the sky♪

11
00:00:46,180 --> 00:00:47,660
♪It said don't bend♪

12
00:00:47,780 --> 00:00:49,820
♪Bow your head, and your chains begin♪

13
00:00:49,940 --> 00:00:51,380
♪You are the wave♪

14
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:53,300
♪And the wind that won't behave♪

15
00:00:53,380 --> 00:00:56,340
♪How could you be chained?♪

16
00:00:56,740 --> 00:00:58,740
♪Untamed, uncaged, unclaimed♪

17
00:00:58,780 --> 00:01:00,540
♪You're the blade in my gaze♪

18
00:01:00,620 --> 00:01:02,420
♪This world will leave you no space♪

19
00:01:02,500 --> 00:01:04,220
♪Then pierce it with your blaze♪

20
00:01:04,220 --> 00:01:06,100
♪My silent grind♪

21
00:01:06,100 --> 00:01:08,060
♪My aching pain♪

22
00:01:08,060 --> 00:01:10,300
♪Will one day turn...♪

23
00:01:11,860 --> 00:01:14,620
♪I am who I am♪

24
00:01:14,620 --> 00:01:18,140
♪My greatest ambition♪

25
00:01:18,220 --> 00:01:21,300
♪If the world can't contain me♪

26
00:01:21,380 --> 00:01:24,940
♪Then I'll break through it♪

27
00:01:25,420 --> 00:01:26,940
♪Become who I am♪

28
00:01:26,940 --> 00:01:28,260
[Wild Ambition Bloom]

29
00:01:28,260 --> 00:01:29,980
[Adapted from Stone and Water's novel,
The Uncaged Flame]

30
00:01:29,980 --> 00:01:32,980
[Episode 4]

31
00:01:33,500 --> 00:01:34,700
How are you so amazing?

32
00:01:35,100 --> 00:01:36,540
Because I'm me.

33
00:01:38,780 --> 00:01:40,620
You should get back to work
in the backyard.

34
00:01:41,340 --> 00:01:42,620
Let me admire you a bit more.

35
00:01:43,220 --> 00:01:44,180
Aren't you going?

36
00:01:44,940 --> 00:01:46,660
Alright then, I'll go help out.

37
00:01:47,580 --> 00:01:48,700
Wait, you're actually going?

38
00:01:53,700 --> 00:01:55,860
Why aren't they back yet?

39
00:02:00,180 --> 00:02:02,860
That's just rude.
You should've waited for your brother.

40
00:02:03,100 --> 00:02:04,220
I'm hungry.

41
00:02:08,260 --> 00:02:09,420
When you went

42
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:11,140
to the apothecary lately,

43
00:02:11,140 --> 00:02:12,860
did you see your sister-in-law?

44
00:02:12,860 --> 00:02:13,980
I saw her at noon today.

45
00:02:15,620 --> 00:02:16,980
Was she

46
00:02:17,380 --> 00:02:18,580
slacking off?

47
00:02:19,220 --> 00:02:20,500
Not sure,

48
00:02:20,500 --> 00:02:21,740
but when I saw her,

49
00:02:22,260 --> 00:02:23,780
she was chatting with a customer
in the front hall.

50
00:02:25,700 --> 00:02:27,060
The front hall?

51
00:02:28,220 --> 00:02:29,860
She was even chatting with a customer?

52
00:02:31,300 --> 00:02:33,540
She's really got it easy.

53
00:02:35,540 --> 00:02:36,660
Then

54
00:02:37,980 --> 00:02:39,780
maybe I should get her

55
00:02:40,140 --> 00:02:40,980
to come back.

56
00:02:42,140 --> 00:02:43,540
I checked the accounts today.

57
00:02:44,380 --> 00:02:45,740
Since you took charge,

58
00:02:46,020 --> 00:02:48,180
our income has been increasing.

59
00:02:48,300 --> 00:02:49,300
Especially yesterday,

60
00:02:49,460 --> 00:02:50,900
it was unprecedentedly high.

61
00:02:52,860 --> 00:02:55,260
We have to thank Mr. Zhang.

62
00:02:55,660 --> 00:02:57,060
He spent a few hundred silver dollars

63
00:02:57,060 --> 00:02:59,540
on seasonal tonics all at once.

64
00:03:01,620 --> 00:03:03,700
If we had a few more customers like him,

65
00:03:04,380 --> 00:03:05,060
Father and I

66
00:03:05,060 --> 00:03:07,220
wouldn't be stressing over the business.

67
00:03:07,860 --> 00:03:08,820
What, Mr. Chen?

68
00:03:09,100 --> 00:03:10,860
Are you satisfied
with just this much money?

69
00:03:12,740 --> 00:03:13,900
What more do you want?

70
00:03:15,340 --> 00:03:16,820
I think we can do even better.

71
00:03:18,180 --> 00:03:19,220
How much better do you want it to be?

72
00:03:20,060 --> 00:03:21,500
Take it easy,
for your sake and the baby's.

73
00:03:21,660 --> 00:03:22,780
Don't push too hard.

74
00:03:22,900 --> 00:03:23,940
But I want to push.

75
00:03:25,300 --> 00:03:27,180
They say greed is never satisfied.

76
00:03:32,020 --> 00:03:32,620
Let's go.

77
00:03:33,780 --> 00:03:34,420
Come on.

78
00:03:39,620 --> 00:03:40,180
Come.

79
00:03:41,060 --> 00:03:41,700
Open the door.

80
00:03:45,580 --> 00:03:46,540
Dashun, Shaohua,

81
00:03:46,860 --> 00:03:47,940
why are you back so late?

82
00:03:48,340 --> 00:03:49,540
Dashun, Shaohua, dig in.

83
00:03:49,860 --> 00:03:50,500
Okay.

84
00:03:51,060 --> 00:03:51,660
Mother,

85
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:53,300
um,

86
00:03:54,060 --> 00:03:55,060
I'll pass.

87
00:03:55,060 --> 00:03:56,740
I'm too tired.

88
00:03:56,900 --> 00:03:58,460
I want to go back and lie down.

89
00:04:00,420 --> 00:04:01,860
How much talking did you do

90
00:04:01,860 --> 00:04:03,380
to wear yourself out like this

91
00:04:04,820 --> 00:04:06,180
and skip dinner on top of it?

92
00:04:07,860 --> 00:04:08,460
Mother,

93
00:04:09,100 --> 00:04:10,500
I want to tell you something.

94
00:04:11,220 --> 00:04:13,260
I don't want to help
at the apothecary anymore.

95
00:04:13,740 --> 00:04:15,100
I want to stay at home.

96
00:04:16,300 --> 00:04:17,580
I had to

97
00:04:17,700 --> 00:04:20,300
slice Jixueteng by myself

98
00:04:20,460 --> 00:04:22,340
and grind pangolin scales.

99
00:04:22,660 --> 00:04:24,300
I couldn't possibly manage it all.

100
00:04:24,940 --> 00:04:26,540
Dashun wouldn't help me either.

101
00:04:26,900 --> 00:04:28,780
I was tied up with customers

102
00:04:28,980 --> 00:04:30,340
and didn't have time to help.

103
00:04:31,540 --> 00:04:32,660
I saw you

104
00:04:32,660 --> 00:04:34,900
chatting with those customers.

105
00:04:34,900 --> 00:04:36,420
I told you to talk to them too.

106
00:04:36,700 --> 00:04:38,900
You said they had bad attitudes,

107
00:04:38,900 --> 00:04:40,780
and when they scolded you,
you couldn't handle it.

108
00:04:42,340 --> 00:04:44,620
Anyway, I'm not going tomorrow.

109
00:04:45,140 --> 00:04:47,260
I worked myself to the bone
and still got yelled at.

110
00:04:54,620 --> 00:04:55,780
Shaohua,

111
00:04:56,700 --> 00:04:57,740
remember, you're not

112
00:04:57,740 --> 00:05:00,700
a spoiled young lady
from a rich household.

113
00:05:01,660 --> 00:05:03,780
You're helping out and doing your part.

114
00:05:04,380 --> 00:05:06,740
Getting scolded a bit
isn't the end of the world.

115
00:05:07,260 --> 00:05:08,020
Mother,

116
00:05:09,060 --> 00:05:11,420
you have no idea
how chaotic it gets at that apothecary.

117
00:05:12,300 --> 00:05:14,620
Anyway, I really can't stand it.

118
00:05:15,260 --> 00:05:17,380
Even if you can't, you have to.

119
00:05:17,700 --> 00:05:18,220
Tomorrow,

120
00:05:18,260 --> 00:05:19,620
you are going to help,

121
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:22,020
no matter what.

122
00:05:22,180 --> 00:05:23,900
Try not to always think
about how to do less.

123
00:05:31,940 --> 00:05:32,860
Okay.

124
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:35,380
Dig in.

125
00:05:35,940 --> 00:05:37,220
Mr. Chen Junior.

126
00:05:37,500 --> 00:05:38,180
Who is it?

127
00:05:38,300 --> 00:05:39,620
Mr. Chen Junior.

128
00:05:39,620 --> 00:05:41,100
You go ahead. I'll check it out.

129
00:05:41,500 --> 00:05:42,860
- Mother, I'll go too.
- Mr. Chen Junior.

130
00:05:42,860 --> 00:05:43,620
You...

131
00:05:44,420 --> 00:05:45,820
- Mr. Chen Junior.
- Coming!

132
00:05:47,140 --> 00:05:47,740
What's wrong, ma'am?

133
00:05:47,740 --> 00:05:48,420
Sir.

134
00:05:48,620 --> 00:05:50,260
Shuan suddenly had a stomachache.

135
00:05:50,500 --> 00:05:51,740
The physician prescribed medicine,

136
00:05:51,820 --> 00:05:53,900
but I ran to several apothecaries,

137
00:05:54,060 --> 00:05:55,100
and they're all closed.

138
00:05:55,380 --> 00:05:56,340
Please help me.

139
00:05:56,380 --> 00:05:57,500
Okay, don't worry.

140
00:05:57,500 --> 00:05:58,300
What medicine do you need?

141
00:05:58,300 --> 00:05:59,660
I'll get it for you.

142
00:05:59,700 --> 00:06:00,540
Thank you.

143
00:06:00,580 --> 00:06:02,260
Go back and eat. Don't wait up.

144
00:06:02,260 --> 00:06:03,060
I'll be back soon.

145
00:06:03,180 --> 00:06:03,900
Let's go.

146
00:06:16,220 --> 00:06:18,220
Shaohua, you've got to eat something.

147
00:06:18,300 --> 00:06:19,140
I just thought

148
00:06:19,140 --> 00:06:20,620
of another trick to boost the business.

149
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:39,720
[Open all night]

150
00:06:39,720 --> 00:06:44,040
[Chen's Apothecary]

151
00:06:54,670 --> 00:06:55,180
[Open all night]

152
00:06:55,180 --> 00:06:57,480
[Decocting medicine for customers,
on-site processing of tonic pastes]

153
00:07:06,580 --> 00:07:07,900
One and a half qian Renshen.

154
00:07:07,900 --> 00:07:09,100
Five qian stir-fried Baizhu.

155
00:07:09,380 --> 00:07:10,460
Three qian Fuling.

156
00:07:10,460 --> 00:07:11,540
Four qian Shanyao.

157
00:07:11,540 --> 00:07:12,500
Five qian lotus seeds.

158
00:07:15,980 --> 00:07:16,660
Zhang Hailong.

159
00:07:17,380 --> 00:07:18,020
Cao Chunsheng.

160
00:07:18,020 --> 00:07:19,020
Please take a seat.

161
00:07:30,700 --> 00:07:31,340
Father,

162
00:07:31,780 --> 00:07:32,900
you're back.

163
00:07:33,860 --> 00:07:34,460
Father.

164
00:07:34,940 --> 00:07:36,300
Weren't you supposed to be back
the day after tomorrow?

165
00:07:36,340 --> 00:07:37,380
Why are you early?

166
00:07:39,100 --> 00:07:41,540
It seems I came back at a bad time.

167
00:07:42,340 --> 00:07:43,340
That's not what I mean.

168
00:07:43,660 --> 00:07:44,500
Please go upstairs.

169
00:07:44,620 --> 00:07:45,740
I'll explain to you.

170
00:07:59,620 --> 00:08:01,340
I was gone for just a few days,

171
00:08:01,780 --> 00:08:03,060
and everything's already a mess?

172
00:08:03,580 --> 00:08:05,020
Father, please don't worry.

173
00:08:05,660 --> 00:08:06,940
Here, take a seat.

174
00:08:08,020 --> 00:08:08,940
Take a look

175
00:08:11,460 --> 00:08:12,220
at the accounts.

176
00:08:21,780 --> 00:08:25,060
The income jumped this much
in just half a month?

177
00:08:25,980 --> 00:08:27,300
Shaohua's the one who made it happen.

178
00:08:28,100 --> 00:08:28,700
Her?

179
00:08:30,060 --> 00:08:31,660
When you weren't here,
we were short-staffed,

180
00:08:31,740 --> 00:08:33,260
so I brought her in to help.

181
00:08:33,820 --> 00:08:34,780
Who would've thought

182
00:08:35,020 --> 00:08:37,460
she actually closed several big orders?

183
00:08:37,620 --> 00:08:38,220
Look,

184
00:08:39,100 --> 00:08:39,820
right here.

185
00:08:40,540 --> 00:08:41,140
Look,

186
00:08:41,900 --> 00:08:43,420
here, those big clients.

187
00:08:45,580 --> 00:08:47,180
They all placed orders

188
00:08:47,180 --> 00:08:49,140
for seasonal tonics
under her persuasion.

189
00:08:52,500 --> 00:08:54,660
What about those two new assistants

190
00:08:54,860 --> 00:08:55,940
we hired?

191
00:08:56,580 --> 00:08:58,540
We promise to stay open all night,

192
00:08:58,540 --> 00:09:00,140
receive prescriptions, deliver medicine,
decoct medicine for customers,

193
00:09:00,260 --> 00:09:01,660
and process tonic pastes at their homes.

194
00:09:02,460 --> 00:09:04,020
We ran short on staff,

195
00:09:04,020 --> 00:09:06,020
so I brought in two new hires.

196
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:08,740
Don't you know,

197
00:09:09,500 --> 00:09:10,460
if we hire people,

198
00:09:11,500 --> 00:09:12,900
we'll have to pay more wages?

199
00:09:13,100 --> 00:09:14,020
But now the business

200
00:09:14,020 --> 00:09:15,660
is more than ten percent
better than before.

201
00:09:20,300 --> 00:09:21,940
This was all Shaohua's idea, wasn't it?

202
00:09:23,340 --> 00:09:23,820
Yes.

203
00:09:28,020 --> 00:09:29,540
She does have a knack for it.

204
00:09:31,140 --> 00:09:31,660
Father,

205
00:09:33,140 --> 00:09:35,660
why don't we let Shaohua come

206
00:09:35,660 --> 00:09:36,780
to help officially?

207
00:09:37,060 --> 00:09:37,860
No way.

208
00:09:38,180 --> 00:09:39,900
We may be struggling,

209
00:09:40,460 --> 00:09:43,180
but we still have our dignity.

210
00:09:43,540 --> 00:09:45,340
Having her help out
in the apothecary like that?

211
00:09:45,420 --> 00:09:46,260
What would that make us?

212
00:09:47,380 --> 00:09:49,300
But Shaohua is really good

213
00:09:49,300 --> 00:09:50,940
at managing the apothecary, Father.

214
00:09:51,660 --> 00:09:53,700
Dashun,

215
00:09:55,140 --> 00:09:56,460
can't she assist you at home

216
00:09:57,420 --> 00:10:00,820
just the same?

217
00:10:02,260 --> 00:10:03,860
Father, I think...

218
00:10:03,980 --> 00:10:05,020
Enough.

219
00:10:05,780 --> 00:10:07,580
It's decided.

220
00:10:08,100 --> 00:10:09,180
I don't want to hear another word.

221
00:10:17,220 --> 00:10:18,460
I don't want to stay at home.

222
00:10:20,860 --> 00:10:21,660
I actually think

223
00:10:22,980 --> 00:10:25,580
staying home
is the right call right now.

224
00:10:26,860 --> 00:10:27,620
Why?

225
00:10:28,260 --> 00:10:28,940
Think about it.

226
00:10:29,660 --> 00:10:31,020
Don't forget you're carrying

227
00:10:31,020 --> 00:10:31,780
a child.

228
00:10:32,100 --> 00:10:33,300
Helping at the apothecary

229
00:10:33,460 --> 00:10:34,940
means early mornings

230
00:10:35,060 --> 00:10:36,300
and late nights.

231
00:10:36,740 --> 00:10:38,100
You'll be rushing
back and forth every day.

232
00:10:38,420 --> 00:10:39,980
What if something goes wrong?

233
00:10:40,820 --> 00:10:41,940
If the baby gets hurt, that's one thing,

234
00:10:42,500 --> 00:10:43,860
but if you get hurt,

235
00:10:44,020 --> 00:10:45,220
I would be devastated.

236
00:10:45,380 --> 00:10:45,980
Dashun,

237
00:10:47,100 --> 00:10:47,900
I'm not afraid of being tired

238
00:10:47,900 --> 00:10:49,140
or going through hardship.

239
00:10:49,900 --> 00:10:50,740
You know that, right?

240
00:10:50,740 --> 00:10:51,700
I do.

241
00:10:51,700 --> 00:10:55,060
I'm afraid that courtyard
will be my whole world

242
00:10:55,060 --> 00:10:55,860
for my whole life.

243
00:10:55,860 --> 00:10:56,720
I know.

244
00:10:56,720 --> 00:10:58,340
That's never going to happen.

245
00:10:58,340 --> 00:10:59,140
Believe me.

246
00:10:59,660 --> 00:11:00,300
I promise,

247
00:11:01,420 --> 00:11:03,740
once you've given birth
and finished your recovery month,

248
00:11:04,580 --> 00:11:06,220
I'll find a way to convince Father

249
00:11:06,660 --> 00:11:07,980
to let you work here.

250
00:11:07,980 --> 00:11:09,500
How much longer will that be?

251
00:11:11,220 --> 00:11:12,340
Just bear with it for a few more months.

252
00:11:21,940 --> 00:11:22,580
Let me take it.

253
00:11:23,060 --> 00:11:25,180
Be good, okay?

254
00:11:35,020 --> 00:11:35,700
Mother,

255
00:11:36,340 --> 00:11:37,620
the hot water is ready.

256
00:11:40,540 --> 00:11:42,900
Since your father-in-law has spoken,

257
00:11:43,380 --> 00:11:44,780
from now on,

258
00:11:45,060 --> 00:11:47,620
don't step out
of this courtyard anymore.

259
00:11:48,260 --> 00:11:50,060
Stay put at home.

260
00:11:53,420 --> 00:11:54,140
Did you hear me?

261
00:11:57,380 --> 00:11:58,940
No sense of occasion either.

262
00:11:59,700 --> 00:12:00,780
Come.

263
00:12:00,780 --> 00:12:02,660
Help me put this hairpin on.

264
00:12:08,020 --> 00:12:08,540
Here.

265
00:12:13,900 --> 00:12:14,460
Give it to me.

266
00:12:15,900 --> 00:12:18,900
Oh my goodness, you poked me.

267
00:12:19,340 --> 00:12:20,500
Never mind.

268
00:12:36,180 --> 00:12:37,700
Why a cold towel?

269
00:12:37,700 --> 00:12:39,380
What am I supposed to do with this?

270
00:12:43,860 --> 00:12:44,580
What?

271
00:12:45,740 --> 00:12:47,620
I barely said anything,

272
00:12:47,620 --> 00:12:48,940
and you're already throwing a fit?

273
00:12:55,020 --> 00:12:57,700
How rebellious!

274
00:12:57,860 --> 00:12:59,140
So what if I am?

275
00:13:00,900 --> 00:13:02,020
Shaohua!

276
00:13:04,980 --> 00:13:05,740
What's wrong?

277
00:13:06,620 --> 00:13:08,420
She was trying to hit me!

278
00:13:08,540 --> 00:13:09,900
How dare she!

279
00:13:12,140 --> 00:13:13,500
Where's my pearl earring?

280
00:13:13,900 --> 00:13:16,660
They cost me three silver dollars!

281
00:13:16,660 --> 00:13:18,500
Can you afford to pay for it?

282
00:13:19,220 --> 00:13:20,340
Don't just stand there.

283
00:13:20,340 --> 00:13:21,500
Help me up!

284
00:13:24,740 --> 00:13:27,100
